Title: The PENITENTS PRESENT themselves.
Description.note: The PENITENTS PRESENT themselves.  The HAIR-SHIRT is put on.  They are turn’d out of CHURCH.  They stand at the church-gate, their TAPERS blown out.  They are led into the CHURCH.  The LITANIES are said, the PENITENTS being on their knees.

Title: The CORPS is CARRIED ALONG.
Description.note: The CORPS is CARRIED ALONG.The CORPS is laid in the CHOIR.  The COFFIN is sprinkled with HOLY-WATER after ‘tis let down in the GRAVE.

Title: A SUN-DEACON ORDAIN'D.
Description.note: A SUN-DEACON ORDAIN'D.DEACON ORDAIN'D.  PRIEST ORDAIN'D.  The PRIEST receives the IMPOSITION of Hands.  The BISHOP impowers the PRIESTS to CONSECRATE.  The BISHOP gives the PRIESTS the SACRAMENT.

Title: The BISHOP elect presents himself with the ASSISTANTS.
Description.note: The BISHOP elect presents himself with the ASSISTANTS.  Takes the OATH.  The BISHOP elect falls PROSTRATE.  Is ANOINTED.  Has his HANDS ANOINTED.  The PASTORAL STAFF given to him.

Title: The BISHOP receives the RING.
Description.note: The BISHOP receives the RING.  The BOOK of the GOSPELS is given him.  The new BISHOP presents the TORCHES, the break & wine.  The MITER put on his HEAD.  The PASTORAL staff given to him.  The ARCHBISHOP receives the PALL.

Title: The ABBOT receives the ECCLESLASTICAL HABIT.
Description.note: The ABBOT receives the ECCLESLASTICAL HABIT.  Receives the IMPOSITION of HANDS.  The ABBESS receives the VEIL.  NUNS CONSECRATED.The HABITS CONSECRATED.They receive the VEIL.

Title: The BISHOP gives the newly consecrated NUNS the RING.
Description.note: The BISHOP gives the newly consecrated NUNS the RING.  The CONSECRATED nuns are crown’d.  The ANATHEMA is READ to them.  The NUNS present TAPERS.  The BISHOP gives the NUNS the COMMUNION.  The BREVIARY is given to them.

Title: The interment of a Pope.
Description.note: The deceased Pope’s corps view’d.  Obsequies of the deceas’d Pope.  The Pope’s corps carries to St. Peter’s Church.  The Pope’s Corps expos’d for 3 days to the view of the people in St. Peter’s Church.  Catafalco or temporary mausoleum erected in honour of the decease’d Pope.  The funeral procession at the Popes interment.
